shift in the role of minorities in AIDS advocacy, policy making and
fund raising across the country. Prominent black organizations and
traditionally black churches have overcome their reticence to take
on the issue, recognizing that the illness in the past decade has
claimed more and more of their own. And accompanying their interest
has been a greater influx of new dollars.
