<P>
   MOVIE NEWS AND REVIEWS
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-TITANS _ Filming wraps this week for ``Remember the
Titans,'' Disney's $10 million-plus movie about the real-life
struggles of a racially plagued high school football team that in
1971 beat all the odds and won Virginia's high school state
championship. We visit the set and talk with producer Jerry
Bruckheimer and the two real-life coaches (one -- Bill Yoast -- was
a former coach at Roswell High School). (BLongino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TITANS-SIDE _ Other films besides ``Remember the Titans'' that
have been filmed or will be made in Georgia, including Sam Raimi's
new flick ``The Gift,'' written by Billy Bob Thornton and starring
Cate Blanchett, that begins filming in Savannah in February.
(BLongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 5.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-ANNA _ Movie review: ``Anna and the King'' with Jodie
Foster and Chow Yun-Fat. (Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
22.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-BIMAN _ Movie review: ``Bicentennial Man'' with Robin
Williams as a robot. Grade: C+. (Murray, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-CIDER _ Movie review: ``Cider House Rules.'' (Murray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-MOTHER _ Movie review: ``All About My Mother.'' (Murray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-DEVIL _ Movie review: ``Ride with the Devil,'' Ang Lee's
film about young guys fighting in Missouri in the Civil War.
(Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-STUART _ Movie review: ``Stuart Little'' the mouse.
(Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
