<P>
   RACE-CRITERIA (Boston) _ In the not-too-distant past, a ruling
striking down the use of race in police department promotions would
have been quickly appealed by a department intent on a diverse
command staff. But the legal landscape has changed dramatically as
the US Supreme Court issued rulings restricting race as criteria in
employment, government contracting and school admissions. By Sacha
Pfeiffer. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   RACISM-CHALLENGE (Boston) _ Horace Seldon, 76, and Ian White
Maher, 27, bridge the generational gap to fight institutional
racism. The two are using their own race to challenge other white
people to see the privileges that come with being white. By Kera
Ritter. 1000 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-SOFTWARE (Undated) _ With just weeks remaining before Jan.
1, 2000, the conventional wisdom about the pending impact of the
Y2K software bug now goes something like this: Party first, fret
later. By Ross Kerber. 1200 words.(a and f coding)
</P>
