<HEADLINE>
HOLIDAY CHAT TO AVOID A SILENT NIGHT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By DIANE WHITE  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The holiday season is upon us. Do you have enough small talk to
see you through the inevitable social gatherings? Here's some
potential conversation fodder.
</P>
<P>
   ``To me, Hillary Clinton represents everything that's right with
America.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I understand you have one of the world's largest collections
of phlogiston.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Forget Richard Gere. Regis Philbin is the sexiest man alive.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Did you know that Dame Edna was one of the original Bond
girls?''
</P>
<P>
   ``For me, Christopher Lydon is funnier than Imus and Stern put
together.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Donald Trump is so terribly misunderstood.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm descended directly from Dracula, on my mother's side.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Larry King is an American treasure.''
</P>
<P>
   ``There's something about Barry Manilow's music that just sends
shivers up and down my spine.''
</P>
<P>
   ``As far as I'm concerned, Jewel is this generation's Emily
Dickinson.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I understand Rosie O'Donnell is really very shy.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't you think Lara Flynn Boyle is a little too old for Jack
Nicholson?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Peter Blute. Now there's my idea of a real man.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just ecstatic that the Judds are back together again.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Whatever happened to Petula Clark?''
</P>
<P>
   ``This year we had a feng shui consultant decorate our Christmas
tree.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Did I ever tell you I dated George W. Bush back in college?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Have you tried my frozen ginger ale salad?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Do you think humankind is headed for some sort of ontological
crisis?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Fat Whacker changed my life.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I never understood what Chet and Natalie saw in each other in
the first place.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Nothing for me, thanks. I'm a Breatharian.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll bet you $100 you can't name the president of Canada.''
</P>
<P>
   `` `Who Wants to be a Millionaire' is fixed. It's obvious.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know what I'm going to do for fun when they finally
finish the Big Dig.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I hear Ricky Martin is a closet heterosexual.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Did you see what Dr. Andrew Weil had to say about incontinence
in the new Modern Maturity?''
</P>
<P>
   `` `The Sopranos' is totally overrated.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I know for a fact that's Upton Bell's own hair. He told me so
himself.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Do you think the Internet is developing a consciousness of its
own?''
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm so glad the millennium comes around just once every
hundred years or so.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A mother is a girl's best friend.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Do you have any Viagra on you that you could loan me?''
</P>
<P>
   ``We're going to miss Quentin Crisp. He was a bridesmaid at our
wedding.''
</P>
<P>
   ``For me, `The Blair Witch Project' was all about spiritual
disenfranchisement.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I might respect Sharon Stone more as an artist if she'd keep
her clothes on.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Life hasn't been the same for me since `Ask the Manager' went
off the air.''
</P>
<P>
   ``This year, I think I'll give up reading Proust for Lent.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
(Diane White is a columnist with The Boston Globe.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
