<P>
   RWANDA-REPORT (United Nations) _ The United Nations and its
member states failed Rwanda in deplorable ways in 1994, ignoring
evidence that a genocide was planned, refusing to act once it was
underway and finally abandoning the Rwandan people when they most
needed protection, according to an independent report commissioned
by Secretary General Kofi Annan and issued on Thursday. By Barbara
Crossette.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-CHECHNYA (Dateline to kum) _ As heavy fighting continues,
refugees stream out of Grozny, the Chechen capital, telling of
hellish conditions in the city. By Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-ELECT (Moscow) _ Political developments/feature before
Parliamentary election on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-IRAQ (Paris) _ What French President Chirac and his
foreign minister have to say about France's position on United
Nations Iraq resolution. By Craig R. Whitney.
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-CHILD-MURDER (London) _ The European Court of Justice
rules that the trial and sentencing of two boys who killed
2-year-old James Bulger was unfair. Lawyers can now request their
release. The killers were 10 at the time and have now served 6
years. By Warren Hoge.
</P>
<P>
   ITALY-ABORTION (Rome) _ Furor in Itay over the legal case of
13-year-old retarded girl in Sicily who is pregnant and whose
parents are seeking an abortion. By Alessandra Stanley.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON &LR;  (``w'' code)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-GAYS (Washington) _ President Clinton addresses the
Democratic National Committee gay and lesbian luncheon in
Washington. By Marc Lacey.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL GENERAL &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   TRIPP-TRIAL (Ellicott City, Md.) _ Monica Lewinsky testifies
that she was frightened when she saw the first published report of
her secretly taped conversations with Linda Tripp about President
Clinton. By Neil A. Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   NEW-ENGLAND-DRUGS (Montpelier, Vt.) _ The New England states,
minus Connecticut, meet to discuss banding together to buy
prescription drugs to cut prices for residents. By Carey Goldberg.
</P>
<P>
   CUBANS-DETAIN (St. Martinville, La.) _ The hostage situation in
Louisiana involving Cuban detainees has underscored once more the
fate of hundreds of Cubans locked in legal limbo in U.S. prisons.
By David Firestone.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS &LR;  (``p'' code)
</P>
