<P>
   WINGS-THEATER-REVIEW (New York) _ Noel Coward's ``Waiting in the
Wings,'' with Rosemary Harris, at the Walter Kerr Theater. Reviewed
by Ben Brantley.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   MET-DESIGN-EXHIBIT (New York) _ Proving once again that it can
mount a boutique of a show with the same panache as a five-alarm
blockbuster, the Metropolitan Museum has unveiled an exquisite
sampling of 20th-century design objects from its own collection. A
salute rather than a full survey, ``A Century of Design, Part I:
1900-1925'' is installed in several intimate galleries in the
20th-century wing. It displays more than 50 examples of furniture,
metalwork, glass, ceramics, textiles, jewelry and drawings, from a
fanciful Pompeiian-style dressing table of bronze and basalt by the
French designer Armand-Albert Rateau to a silver claret jug with
sinuous curves and flyaway thumb-piece, the work of the English
craftsman Archibald Knox. By Grace Glueck.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-CRITICS-AWARDS (New York) _ The New York Film Critics
awards are to be announced. By Kathryn Shattuck.
</P>
