   FBN-CARRUTH (Charlotte) _ Rae Carruth, the Carolina Panthers'
wide receiver, was being held in the Madison County, Tenn., jail on
a federal charge of unlawful flight to avoid prosecution, and an
extradition hearing was scheduled. Carruth vanished from Charlotte
on Tuesday, when a warrant was issued charging him with
first-degree murder in the shooting death of his girlfriend,
Cherica Adams. She died earlier that day from wounds suffered in a
Nov. 16 attack as she drove her car in a Charlotte suburb.
