<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
  
 AT THE END of the CENTURY ... HOW DO AMERICANS FEEL ABOUT
THEMSELVES and THEIR LIVES?  
 &HT;     (To publish this special New York Times Millennium Poll as a
``separate buy'' feature, it must be purchased from one of these
New York Times Syndicate sales representatives: 
 &HT;    (--U.S. and Canada: DEBRA WEYDERT in New Jersey at
1-732-390-4480; fax, 732-390-4697. 
 &HT;    (--Europe and Asia: KARL HORWITZ in Paris at 47-42-17-11; fax,
47-42-80-44 or 47-42-18-81; telex, 282-942. 
 &HT;    (--Latin America: OLIVIA VASQUEZ in Los Angeles, 310-798-0970;
fax, 310-798-7338.)  c.1999 The New York Times Magazine  
<TEXT>
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QC;
<P>
   ON THE EVE OF THE MILLENNIUM, Americans are concentrating on
their own families and are relatively less involved with their
communities outside the home.
</P>
<P>
   A large majority of the public believes it's critical to have
the power to stand up for oneself and be able to communicate one's
feelings. Being a good neighbor is given more priority than
community involvement or having a lot of friends. And having
children is deemed more important than being married.
</P>
<P>
   Thanks to good economic times, there is a general feeling of
optimism about the future for most Americans. That optimism,
however, is joined by considerable concern about the morals of this
country.
</P>
<P>
   Peace and quiet _ time for onesself _ is seen as in short supply
these days. Getting time for oneself is an important wish for the
future.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; -0- &QL;
</P>
<P>
   __ ABOUT the SURVEY: The New York Times Millennium Poll was
conducted by the News Surveys department of The New York Times. It
was designed by MARJORIE CONNELLY, staff editor, under the
direction of MICHAEL KAGAY, head of the department. A total of
1,178 adult Americans were interviewed by telephone between July 17
and July 19, 1999. The sampling error in the poll could account for
variations of plus or minus 3 percentage points in major findings.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; -0- &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1. How likely do you think it is that today's youth will have a
better life than their parents?
</P>
<P>
   Very likely..................29
</P>
<P>
   Somewhat likely..............42
</P>
<P>
   Somewhat unlikely............18
</P>
<P>
   Very unlikely.................8
</P>
<P>
   Don't know-Not applicable.....3
</P>
<P>
   2. What do you consider to be the one best thing about yourself?
</P>
<P>
   Looks.........................--
</P>
<P>
   Personality...................26
</P>
<P>
   Intelligence...................2
</P>
<P>
   Sense of humor.................1
</P>
<P>
   Faith..........................7
</P>
<P>
   Education......................3
</P>
<P>
   Work ethic, career.............13
</P>
<P>
   Parenting skills..............12
</P>
<P>
   Ability to adapt...............4
</P>
<P>
   Honesty, integrity.............10
</P>
<P>
   Volunteer work.................1
</P>
<P>
   Health.........................4
</P>
<P>
   Other..........................5
</P>
<P>
   DK-NA.........................10
</P>
<P>
   3. If you could change one thing about yourself, what would it
be?
</P>
<P>
   Weight loss....................7
</P>
<P>
   Better body....................1
</P>
<P>
   Hair loss.....................--
</P>
<P>
   Other physical changes
</P>
<P>
   ....(e.g., hair-eye color, smaller
</P>
<P>
   .... thighs)...................3
</P>
<P>
   Health.........................4
</P>
<P>
   Residence......................2
</P>
<P>
   Personality in general.........4
</P>
<P>
   Attitude.......................4
</P>
<P>
   More patience, less anger......5
</P>
<P>
   More assertive, confident......4
</P>
<P>
   Better education..............14
</P>
<P>
   Employment, ambition...........3
</P>
<P>
   Better organized...............5
</P>
<P>
   Better person in general
</P>
<P>
   ....(helpful, considerate,
</P>
<P>
   ....tolerant)..................5
</P>
<P>
   Family relationships...........2
</P>
<P>
   Money..........................6
</P>
<P>
   Age............................4
</P>
<P>
   Smoking........................2
</P>
<P>
   More spiritual, religious.......1
</P>
<P>
   Nothing........................5
</P>
<P>
   Other..........................1
</P>
<P>
   DK-NA.........................18
</P>
<P>
   4. How important to you is having enough time for yourself?
</P>
<P>
   Very important.................52
</P>
<P>
   Somewhat important.............38
</P>
<P>
   Not very important..............8
</P>
<P>
   Not at all important............2
</P>
<P>
   5. How important to you is being involved in your community?
</P>
<P>
   Very important.................35
</P>
<P>
   Somewhat important.............51
