<P>
   FBC-HERITAGE _ Participating in the Heritage Bowl will be a
homecoming of sorts for Hampton quarterback Roy Johnson. Johnson
was a standout high school quarterback in metro Atlanta and will
lead Hampton into Saturday's McDonald's Heritage Bowl against
Southern University. (Reese, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFL-PREVIEW _ What to look for this weekend in the NFL.
(Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   BOXING
</P>
<P>
   BOX-HOLYFIELD-DIVORCE _ Judge Ben Miller orders the Rev. Creflo
Dollar to appear in the Fayette County Courthouse at 10:30 a.m.
Dec. 21 to give a deposition in the Evander Holyfield divorce case.
His lawyer won't predict if Dollar will show up, but if he doesn't
he'll be held in contempt, the judge says. Dollar, leader of World
Changers church, has fought the deposition, partly on grounds of
church-state separation. The high-stakes divorce trial is now set
for April 3. (Ellis, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
