   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   MCCAIN-BRADLEY _ CLAREMONT, N.H. _ In an historic encounter,
Sen. John McCain and former New Jersey Senator Bill Bradley, both
vying for their party's nomination, will meet at a public forum to
discuss campaign finance reform. The forum will take place in
Claremont, N.H., where President Clinton and Newt Gingrich pledged
to enact campaign finance reform in 1995. The former colleagues
will also hold a joint news conference following the event.
(Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
