   BUSH-HISPANICS _ (Developing) Months after he garnered criticism
for saying no to speaking invitations from some of the nation's
most prominent Hispanic groups, Gov. George W. Bush continues his
assiduous courting of Latino supporters in his own way, employing a
pro-business style designed to win votes _ and money. (Heath,
Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
