<HEADER>
A1130 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r v BC-TEXBUDGET-TEX     12-16 0295
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TEXBUDGET-TEX </SLUG>
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Fort Worth Star-Telegram plans to move the following stories
for clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Friday,
Dec. 17, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Lou
Hudson, Carmelita Bevill or Jim Peipert on the Star-Telegram's
National/Foreign Desk at (817) 390-7785. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   N A T I O N A L &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MCCONAL-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ALVARADO, Texas _ Trinidad De La Cruz is one of eight people in
the world who can make a Rolls Royce grill. At least that is what a
television commercial said about him a few years ago. That does
make him special when it comes to auto body work. And right now,
he's engaged in a special job. He is restoring the Cadillac hearse
that carried the casket and body of President John F. Kennedy from
Parkland Hospital in Dallas to Love Field to be flown to Washington
after his assassination in Dallas in 1963. By JON MCCONAL. Story
has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   E N T E R T A I N M E N T &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CHRISTMAS CDS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ It's beginning to look a lot like everyone will
release a Christmas CD this year. What to buy, and what to banish.
By DAVE FERMAN, SHIRLEY JINKINS and MALCOLM MAYHEW. Story will move
in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F I N A N C I A L &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BIZBOOKS-REVIEWS &QL;
</P>
