<HEADER>
A1134 &Cx1f; tab-z
r k BC-GOOFBALL-AWARDS-1990S     12-16 1818
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GOOFBALL-AWARDS-1990S-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
  
 THE GOOF AWARD of the DECADE!!!  
 &HT;     (This has already moved to clients of Richard Roeper's popular
weekly columns, now being offered as a regular New York Times
Syndicate feature. For a bio &AMP; photo _ as well as special contract
rates _ please contact your sales representative:
 &HT;    (--U.S. and Canada: DEBRA WEYDERT in New Jersey at 732-390-4480;
fax, 732-390-4697. 
 &HT;    (--Latin America: OLIVIA VASQUEZ in Los Angeles, 310-798-0970;
fax, 310-798-7338.)  By RICHARD ROEPER  
 c.1999 The Chicago Sun-Times  
<TEXT>
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QC;
<P>
   This is the time of the year when I usually announce the lucky
recipient of the annual GOOF (Greatly Overexposed and Overhyped
Fool) Award, a gigantic trophy made entirely of goat cheese carved
into the image of the original winners, Milli Vanilli.
</P>
<P>
   The GOOF recognizes the scandalous and the shameless, the silly
and the sinful. In the last three years, the winners have been
DENNIS RODMAN, JERRY SPRINGER and MONICA LEWINSKY/LINDA TRIPP,
respectively. You get the idea.
</P>
<P>
   As always, there was no shortage of worthy contenders in 1999,
from JESSE ``The Oddity'' VENTURA to PAMELA ANDERSON SOMETIMES-LEE
to EMINEM to DONALD TRUMP to JAR-JAR BINKS. Normally we'd give each
of these nominees a little write-up, but we've got a whole decade
to deal with here _ so we'll dispense with the speeches and get
right to the opening of the envelope.
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Award for the Year &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   And the GOOF for 1999 goes to:
</P>
<P>
   The entire cast of ``The Real World: Hawaii''!
(Clap-clap-clap-clap-clap-clap-clap ...)
</P>
<P>
   Never before have we seen such a self-indulgent, self-important,
self-destructive yet telegenic bunch of TV brats. Way to go, kids!
Each week there was a new train wreck of an adventure _ Ruthie the
alcoholic lesbian needs to be rescued by paramedics after passing
out in the shower! Teck and Kaia go skinnydipping in the Jacuzzi!
Ruthie cavorts with Kaia in the cab! Colin and Amaya get it on,
then break up. Amaya chases one of Colin's buddies! Kaia moves on
Matt, who's smitten with Ruthie's twin sister! Meanwhile, Justin _
the gay law student with the mood hair _ flees the house ...
Puleeeeeaaaaasssse!
 &UR; Scandal-Stars of the '90s &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   AND NOW for the most decadent scandal-stars of the '90s! What a
glittering list of nominees! Please hold your applause _ and your
nostalgic guffaws _ until all the deserving candidates have been
announced.
</P>
<P>
   -- MARION BARRY: Kicked off the decade on a high note when he
was arrested Jan. 19, 1990. The FBI had videotaped him lighting up
a crack pipe in a Washington, D.C., hotel room. Five words that
will live in infamy: ``The b--ch set me up!''
</P>
<P>
   -- PEE-WEE HERMAN: Other celebrities have recovered from more
serious scandals, but after Pee-wee (real name: Paul Reubens) was
caught using himself as his own personal playhouse in a movie
theater in 1991, he disappeared and hasn't been able to recapture
the public's imagination, despite a recurring guest role on
``Murphy Brown'' and several movie roles.
</P>
<P>
   -- JERRY SPRINGER: If he were as pompous as a DR. LAURA
SCHLESSINGER or as sanctimonious as a RUSH LIMBAUGH, Jerry might be
a prime contender for GOOF of the 1990s. But he admits he's the
ringmaster of a circus freak show. That makes it hard to get really
mad at him. Nevertheless, anyone who parades that many jiggling,
trash-talking, cross-dressing cat-fighters in front of a national
audience deserves a GOOF Awards Committee Special Commendation.
</P>
<P>
   -- JENNY JONES: She's a deer-in-the-headlights version of
SPRINGER who doesn't seem to comprehend what she's gotten herself
into and seems incapable of explaining why she keeps hosting her
depressingly trashy show.
</P>
<P>
   -- MICHAEL JACKSON: In the most unholy union in show business
history, the Man in the Surgical Mask married LISA MARIE PRESLEY,
who displayed all the enthusiasm of a PATTY HEARST in the early
days with the SLA. After that marriage crumbled, Jackson wed his
plastic surgeon's nurse and had two children _ Paris and Prince _
before another split-up.
</P>
<P>
   -- KATHIE LEE GIFFORD: Blabber-mouthed Kathie Lee was
temporarily rendered speechless amid all the snickering about her
waxen hunk of a husband, FRANK, groping a busty flight attendant
while a tabloid rag's hidden camera clicked away. She also had to
weather a torrent of negative publicity about her signature line of
clothing being produced in sweatshops _ leading to the bizarre
spectacle of hubbie Frank showing up at one such factory in New
York's Garment District with a bag of cash, which he handed out to
puzzled but grateful workers.
</P>
<P>
   -- LATRELL SPREWELL: This entire column could be filled with a
roster of athletes who disgraced themselves and their sport with
their antics, but we'll let Spree's name represent all the selfish
and stupid jocks whose names landed on the scandal blotter in the
'90s. A top athlete is sometimes referred to as a ``player's
player.'' Spree is a jerk's jerk.
</P>
<P>
   -- DAN RATHER: He's one of the most respected journalists of the
20th century _ and one of the wackiest TV personalities ever.
``Gunga Dan's'' emotional, meandering, iron-man high-wire act on
the weekend of JOHN KENNEDY JR.'s death was one of the most
fascinating pieces of performance art in TV history.
</P>
<P>
   -- DONALD TRUMP: Reacted to the news of PRINCESS DIANA's death
by lamenting that he never got the chance to sleep with her.
Visited a public school in an impoverished neighborhood and dropped
a phony $1 million bill into a donation box as a joke. Dumped MARLA
MAPLES before a prenup clause could kick in, and started dating a
series of idiot models. Actually boasted about the sleazy rock
stars who were trying to have sex with his 15-year-old model
daughter IVANKA. Threatened to run for president, just because.
</P>
<P>
   And he still has the bad hair.
</P>
<P>
   -- SPICE GIRLS: Not since Josie and the Pussycats have so many
chicks done so much with so little talent.
 &UR; Frontrunning GOOF Couples &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Many of the frontrunners for the big GOOF were fun, and
sometimes not-so-fun, couples:
</P>
<P>
   -- JOEY BUTTAFUOCO and AMY FISHER: At 16, ``The Long Island
Lolita'' proved her love for Buttafuoco by shooting his wife in the
head. And they say kids that age aren't capable of making a
commitment.
</P>
<P>
   -- WILLIAM KENNEDY SMITH and PATRICIA ``Blue Dot'' BOWMAN: The
televised trial and acquittal of Smith _ who was accused of
sexually assaulting Bowman on a Florida beach near the Kennedy
compound after a night of partying with UNCLE TEDDY _ was the first
courtroom media circus of the decade, and set the tone for the
hysterical coverage of subsequent sensational cases.
</P>
<P>
   -- CLARENCE THOMAS and ANITA HILL: He was a nominee for the U.S.
Supreme Court and she was the former staffer who nearly derailed
his appointment in a wild hearing that included mentions of pubic
hairs on cans of Coke, ``The Exorcist'' and one Long Dong Silver,
porn star extraordinaire.
</P>
<P>
   -- WOODY ALLEN and MIA FARROW: Serial adopter Farrow was
horrified to learn that one of her daughters was shacking up with
the formerly funny but now mostly creepy Woody.
</P>
<P>
   -- NANCY KERRIGAN and TONYA HARDING: For one shining moment,
figure skating was as entertaining as the World Wrestling
Federation.
</P>
<P>
   -- JOHN and LORENA BOBBITT: The feisty manicurist temporarily
separated her allegedly abusive husband from his most intimate
organ in the slice-and-dice heard 'round the world.
</P>
<P>
   -- HUGH GRANT and DIVINE BROWN: Grant proved he was clinically
insane by risking his longtime relationship with the otherworldly
ELIZABETH HURLEY for a street corner encounter with a cheap hooker.
</P>
<P>
   -- MARY KAY LETOURNEAU and VILI FUALAAU: The schoolteacher and
the under-age student she seduced now have two children _ which
means that when she's about 50, he'll just be turning 30, and their
kids will be teen-agers. Wacky!
</P>
<P>
   -- MARCIA CLARK and JOHNNIE COCHRAN: He was the nattily attired,
grandstanding defense attorney who delivered the jury to O.J.
SIMPSON. She was the strident, overworked prosecutor who fumbled
more times in the courtroom than Simpson did in his entire career.
You know, there's a fine line between bickering and love; I think
JUDGE ITO should have married those two while he had the chance.
</P>
<P>
   -- ELLEN DeGENERES and ANNE HECHE: They might have gained more
public support if they hadn't practically felt each other up in
front of PRESIDENT CLINTON and acted as if publicizing their
relationship was the biggest act of bravery under duress this side
of Oskar Schindler.
</P>
<P>
   -- BILL CLINTON and GENNIFER FLOWERS: (Not to mention Clinton
and MONICA LEWINSKY. And Clinton and ELIZABETH WARD GRACEN. And
Clinton and HILLARY CLINTON. And Clinton and JANE DOE No. 1.) Let's
just put it this way: If WARREN BEATTY somehow became president,
we'd see more of a traditional family situation in the White House
with that Hollywood lothario in the big chair than we did with the
Clintons in the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
   So how about a BIG round of applause? For sheer depth of
depravity, the 1990s were perhaps unmatched _ with the possible
exceptions of the 1920s and, oh yeah, the 1170s (... you remember
them).
 &UR; GOOF of the Decade &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   On this, there really wasn't much debate, as one man stood above
the rest as the centerpiece of the dominant scandal-story of this
or any other decade in the 20th century.
</P>
<P>
   His name, of course --- is O.J. SIMPSON. (Clap-clap-clap! Wait
... On second thought, let's not clap.)
</P>
<P>
   In June 1994, the former football great turned grade-B celebrity
either murdered his ex-wife Nicole and her friend Ronald Goldman or
was framed by the Los Angeles Police Department in the most
wide-ranging conspiracy since 1963. For more than two years, one
jaw-dropping spectacle after another played out, from the
handcuffing of O.J. to the white Bronco chase to the endless
criminal trial to the civil judgment, with supporting players such
as KATO KAELIN, MARK FUHRMAN, F. LEE BAILEY, PAULA BARBIERI and
FRED GOLDMAN taking their turns on the side stages.
</P>
<P>
   As for O.J., he continues his search for the real killers, who
apparently are hiding out on public golf courses or in the
brassiere of the occasional stupid young blond woman who
idiotically finds him attractive.
</P>
<P>
   Congratulations, O.J!
</P>
<P>
   You're the runaway winner of the GOOF Award for the 1990s.
Here's hoping you don't have to auction it off, as you did the
Heisman.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Richard Roeper (rroeper &LR; suntimes.com) is a columnist for the
Chicago Sun-Times, the author of ``Urban Legends: The Truth Behind
All Those Deliciously Entertaining Myths That Are Absolutely,
Positively, 100% Not True!'' and co-author of ``He Rents, She
Rents.'') &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ----------------- &QC;
</P>
</TEXT>
