<SLUG> BC-COKE-SUPERBOWL-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    ACVB, Coke bottler promo a first
 &HT;    By Shelia M. Poole
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Those familiar red and white cartons of Coke will soon
contain a little something extra for consumers .
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta Coca-Cola Bottling Co. has teamed up with the
Atlanta Convention &AMP; Visitors Bureau for a joint marketing program
to promote the city and some of its top tourist attractions.
</P>
<P>
   Beginning Dec. 27, more than 8,000 stores in Georgia will sell
special 12-can packs of Coke that sport a Super Bowl theme and
contain the Atlanta Convention &AMP; Visitors Bureau logo. Inside the
1.4 million packs will be special commemorative Super Bowl XXXIV
cans.
</P>
<P>
   Additionally, each pack will include an ``Around Atlanta''
discount book, including coupons to the NFL Experience, the World
of Coca-Cola and Underground Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   If coupons aren't enough, three winning game pieces good for
tickets to Super Bowl XXXV in Tampa in 2001 have been randomly
placed inside the Around Atlanta booklet.
</P>
<P>
   This may the first time the bottling company has joined a
convention and visitors bureau in a packaging promotion in the
United States, said Dan Lee, the company's director of marketing.
</P>
<P>
   The partnership began nearly a year ago. ``We started working on
a plan on how we both could benefit from a consumer promotion,''
Lee said. The company has relationships with many of the
attractions in the area, and the bureau helps promote many of them,
he said. ``It seemed a natural fit to bring all of us together.''
</P>
<P>
   Lee said the bottling company and the bureau will likely work on
other joint programs. Projects could include ``combining our forces
within the hotel, motel and restaurant industry.''
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta Coca-Cola Bottling Co. is a division of Coca-Cola
Enterprises.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
