<P>
   (NYT10) WASHINGTON -- Dec. 16, 1999 - MIDEAST-TALKS-4 -- From
left, National Security Advisory Sandy Berger, Israeli Attorney
General Ellie Rubenstein, Secretary of State Madeleine Albright,
and Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy look on during a brief
statement that was made by President Clinton after the conclusions
of talks Thursday between Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak and
Syrian Foreign Minister Farouk al-Sharaa. Israel and Syria ended
two days of inconclusive peace talks Thursday which they agreed to
