<SLUG> BC-POLITICS-LAUTENBERG-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LAUTENBERG TO ENDORSE GORE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JILL ZUCKMAN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANCHESTER, N.H. _ In an effort to embarrass Bill Bradley here
in the first-in-the-nation primary state, Vice President Al Gore's
campaign will announce Friday that New Jersey Senator Frank
Lautenberg is endorsing Gore for president.
</P>
<P>
   Lautenberg will also attend Friday's Democratic town hall forum
at Daniel Webster College in Nashua, in a show of support for the
vice president.
</P>
<P>
   During a telephone interview Thursday, Lautenberg said he had
had ``much more contact'' with Gore over the years than with
Bradley, a former New Jersey senator who served with Lautenberg. He
said he had committed to support Gore well before Bradley ever told
him he would be getting into the race.
</P>
<P>
   When asked what decision he would have made if he had known
Bradley was going to run, Lautenberg said, ``All things being as
they are, I would choose Al Gore again.''
</P>
<P>
   Lautenberg praised Gore for his work on the environment and
education, and said his experience in the Senate and the vice
presidency made him most qualified to be president.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't want to embarrass Bill Bradley,'' Lautenberg said.
``Should things go against my candidate and Bill Bradley's the
nominee, I think I could very comfortably support Bill Bradley.''
</P>
</TEXT>
