<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, Dec. 17. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
STADIUM _ The Tostitos Fiesta Bowl is willing to help finance a new
Valley football stadium, but the amount it commits depends on the
kind of deal assembled in the coming months, the bowl's executive
director said Thursday. Also Thursday, the task force accepted
proposals on proposed stadium sites in Tempe and Phoenix. Story
will move in the ``A'' and ``S'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
TRIBE-CASINO _ Faced with an uproar among tribal members who say
they aren't getting their fair share, the Salt River Pima-Maricopa
Indian Community unveiled its annual budget, $68 million, a $25
million increase since the tribe opened its two casinos 18 months
ago. Tribal leaders handed out copies of tribal finances for the
first time during a volatile debate &UR; over a proposal to give members
a cut of the profit from the tribe's two casinos. Story will move
in the ``A'' category. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
